---
title: Zucchini Flatbreads with Balsamic Onions, Olives, and Walnuts
description: This recipe is all about the technique: here, you’ll be practicing cutting zucchini into paper-thin ribbons with a vegetable peeler. When baked into this toasty flatbread, they’ll make for a picture-perfect presentation that’s aided by the brilliant colors of the red onions and black olive rings.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/zucchini-and-ricotta-flatbread-0d6b8337.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/zucchini-and-ricotta-flatbread-f1db6deb.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/zucchini-flatbreads-583318db7d69bf38437b9a22
servings: 2
time required: 30 minutes
author: HelloFresh
cuisine: North America
nutrition:
  calories: 682 kcal
  fat: 27 g
  saturated fat: 4 g
  carbohydrates: 67 g
  sugar: 18 g
  protein: 24 g
  fiber: 7 g
  sodium: 995 mg
course: main course
---

Wash and dry all produce. Preheat oven to 450 degrees. Halve, peel, and thinly slice
@red onion{1}(halved, peeled, and thinly sliced). Trim ends from @zucchini{1}, then peel on
all sides into ribbons with a #vegetable peeler{}, stopping before you reach seedy core.
Discard core. Slice @black olives{1%ounce} into rounds. Thinly slice
@sun-dried tomatoes{1.5%ounce}(thinly sliced).

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tablespoon} in a #medium pan{} over medium-high heat.
Add onion and 1 TBSP @balsamic vinegar{2%tablespoon}. Cook until caramelized,
~{3-5%minutes}, stirring occasionally. Remove from heat.

Stir @dried thyme{1%teaspoon} into @ricotta cheese{4%ounce} in a #small bowl{}. Season
generously with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Place @flatbreads{2} on a lightly oiled #baking sheet{}. Spread ricotta sauce on each
flatbread in a thin layer. Top with zucchini, olives, sun-dried tomatoes, caramelized
onions, and @walnuts{1%ounce}. Bake until zucchini is crisp and flatbreads are lightly
browned, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Combine 1 tsp @Dijon mustard{1%jar} and 1 TBSP balsamic vinegar in a #large bowl{}.
Whisk in a drizzle of olive oil and season with salt and pepper. Add
@mixed greens{3%ounce} and toss to combine.

Slice flatbreads into quarters. Serve with salad.

> This recipe is all about the technique: here, you'll be practicing cutting zucchini into
> paper-thin ribbons with a vegetable peeler. When baked into this toasty flatbread,
> they'll make for a picture-perfect presentation that's aided by the brilliant colors
> of the red onions and black olive rings.